pageContext.claim: “But when you take that [New York, New Jersey] out [of the number of deaths from covid-19], our numbers are among the lowest. And even with it in -- I will get back to you, but we have among the lowest numbers. They've done a fantastic job on it.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. Even removing the roughly 50,000 people who died of covid-19 in New York and New Jersey, the U.S. has still seen more people die of the disease than any other country around the world.
